<p>Typically, writers use these â€œthoughtâ€ verbs at the beginning of a paragraph (In this form, you can call them â€œThesis Statementsâ€ and Iâ€™ll rail against those, later). In a way, they state the intention of the paragraph. And what follows, illustrates them.</p>

