<p>Instead of bland â€œisâ€ and â€œhasâ€ statements, try burying your details of what a character has or is, in actions or gestures. At its most basic, this is showing your story instead of telling it.</p>

<p>And forever after, once youâ€™ve learned to un-pack your characters, youâ€™ll hate the lazy writer who settles for:</p>

